00:00:53,588 --> 00:00:57,323
narrator: spinning reels are also called fixed spool reels.   

10
00:00:57,325 --> 00:01:01,126
that's because the spool on this
fishing reel doesn't rotate.  

11
00:01:01,128 --> 00:01:04,330
instead, a device around the spool does the spinning,  

12
00:01:04,332 --> 00:01:06,465
which winds the fishing line. 

13
00:01:06,467 --> 00:01:08,867
the advantage of using a non-spinning spool      

14
00:01:08,869 --> 00:01:13,138
is there's no backlash of the line.          

15
00:01:13,140 --> 00:01:16,341
a spinning reel provides a unique twist on fishing.   

16
00:01:16,343 --> 00:01:19,612
unlike other reels, the spool doesn't rotate.   

17
00:01:19,614 --> 00:01:22,047
instead, a pivoting, u-shaped wire         

18
00:01:22,049 --> 00:01:27,219
called a bail spins around the spool to wrap the line.  

19
00:01:27,221 --> 00:01:28,554
making a spinning reel     

20
00:01:28,556 --> 00:01:32,024
starts with a cylindrical chunk of aluminum.       

21
00:01:32,026 --> 00:01:35,361
computerized cutters carve the cylinder into the rotor  

22
00:01:35,363 --> 00:01:38,898
that spins the bail around the reel spool.     

23
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:41,834
the transformation is complete.

24
00:01:41,836 --> 00:01:45,905
the cutter sculpts side arms  
onto the rotor to hold the bail,

25
00:01:45,907 --> 00:01:48,774
carving a hole for the spool shaft.      

26
00:01:48,776 --> 00:01:51,777
then a protective finish is applied to the rotor,    

27
00:01:51,779 --> 00:01:54,246
and the bail is attached.   

28
00:01:54,248 --> 00:01:57,383
next, a craftsman heats a cylindrical piece of steel  

29
00:01:57,385 --> 00:02:00,919
in a furnace until it's hot and flexible.  

30
00:02:00,921 --> 00:02:02,654
then it's transferred over to a press           

31
00:02:02,656 --> 00:02:05,323
that flattens the cylinder.  

32
00:02:05,325 --> 00:02:09,128
the worker inserts the hot steel puck into a mold.    

33
00:02:09,130 --> 00:02:13,465
the top half descends and forces
the steel into the crevices.  

34
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:15,601
tools cut teeth into the part, 

35
00:02:15,603 --> 00:02:18,871
completing the transformation into a gear.          

36
00:02:18,873 --> 00:02:23,075
next, the gear housing is formed
using aluminum alloy.     

37
00:02:23,077 --> 00:02:26,011
to trim the excess material from around the edges,     

38
00:02:26,013 --> 00:02:28,146
designers use a die cutter.  

39
00:02:28,148 --> 00:02:29,748
it punches down a part,    

40
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:32,951
which then slides down a chute into a bin.          

41
00:02:32,953 --> 00:02:36,088
at another station, a laser etches the company name    

42
00:02:36,090 --> 00:02:38,324
and the product number into the part.         

43
00:02:41,095 --> 00:02:43,796
the gear system is now ready to be assembled.        

44
00:02:48,235 --> 00:02:53,172
the technician brushes oil on a transmission gear...   

45
00:02:53,174 --> 00:02:55,240
installs it in the gear housing

46
00:02:55,242 --> 00:02:56,876
and screws it in place.    

47
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:05,184
next, a part called a slider is placed on top of the gear. 

48
00:03:05,186 --> 00:03:06,852
the ends of the slider are attached          

49
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:09,955
to the spinning reel body using thick pins.       

50
00:03:13,194 --> 00:03:15,194
the slider moves the spool up 

51
00:03:15,196 --> 00:03:18,064
and down as the bail spins the line.        

52
00:03:20,201 --> 00:03:22,801
oil is applied onto the neck of the gear body,       

53
00:03:22,803 --> 00:03:27,339
and a helical pinion is inserted into the gear.   

54
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:29,941
next, the technician installs a roller element        

55
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:32,878
on the extended part of the pinion gear.      

56
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:35,548
a retaining ring is positioned between the bearing      

57
00:03:35,550 --> 00:03:39,151
and the gear body.       

58
00:03:39,153 --> 00:03:40,753
then a wider steel ring    

59
00:03:40,755 --> 00:03:45,224
is placed onto the outside of the neck. 

60
00:03:45,226 --> 00:03:49,161
an outer metal sleeve holds the part together.    

61
00:03:49,163 --> 00:03:53,833
the threaded end of the pinion gear is set on top. 

62
00:03:53,835 --> 00:03:57,236
next, the rotor is attached on the end of the pinion gear 

63
00:03:57,238 --> 00:04:00,906
and secured with a nut.    

64
00:04:00,908 --> 00:04:03,042
this connects the rotor to the gear.          

65
00:04:05,713 --> 00:04:10,849
the rotor is tested to confirm that it's operating smoothly. 

66
00:04:10,851 --> 00:04:14,519
another operator places the main gear in the gear body 

67
00:04:14,521 --> 00:04:18,457
so that the lower teeth engage with the other gears.     

68
00:04:18,459 --> 00:04:22,294
the operator slides a metal washer on the gear shaft    

69
00:04:22,296 --> 00:04:26,965
and links a main axle shaft to the slider.         

70
00:04:26,967 --> 00:04:30,369
the operator screws the end of the shaft to the slider... 

71
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:37,209
...and inserts thick pins into the gear housing.     

72
00:04:37,211 --> 00:04:38,577
they'll prevent the main gear 

73
00:04:38,579 --> 00:04:40,946
from turning in the wrong direction.    

74
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:45,818
the spinning reel gear system is now complete.        

75
00:04:45,820 --> 00:04:50,289
next, an operator attaches a side plate to the gear body. 

76
00:04:50,291 --> 00:04:53,491
this encases the spinning reel's gear system.      

77
00:04:53,493 --> 00:04:55,561
the threaded fitting will enable
the gears           

78
00:04:55,563 --> 00:04:57,429
to be linked to a handle.   

79
00:04:57,431 --> 00:05:02,701
♪♪         

80
00:05:02,703 --> 00:05:05,704
the reel spool has a drag system inside         

81
00:05:05,706 --> 00:05:07,906
so the line will slip instead of breaking      

82
00:05:07,908 --> 00:05:11,043
when pulled by a powerful fish.

83
00:05:11,045 --> 00:05:15,414
a drag adjustment knob is   
screwed to the end of the spool,

84
00:05:15,416 --> 00:05:17,850
then the technician fastens the handle       

85
00:05:17,852 --> 00:05:19,685
to the fitting in the gear body

86
00:05:19,687 --> 00:05:22,588
and checks to confirm it operates smoothly.     

87
00:05:25,793 --> 00:05:28,727
an automated testing system turns the handle        

88
00:05:28,729 --> 00:05:31,529
while water flows over the gear body.      

89
00:05:31,531 --> 00:05:33,198
this exposes any leaks     

90
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:36,068
that could compromise the internal gear system.   

91
00:05:38,806 --> 00:05:42,808
finally, this spinning reel is ready for action.      

92
